# Fuel-Pro (React)

Multi-tenant fuel-station admin app. **React 18 + Vite + react-router-dom**, vanilla **SCSS** (the reused Colorlib theme). No Bootstrap, no jQuery, no Tailwind/PostCSS, no extra state library. Pages render mock data from `src/data/mock/`; real endpoints go through `src/api/`.

Keep this always-applied rule small. Use project skills for detail:

- `token-lean-workflow` â€” token-conscious search, editing, verification, summaries.
- `fuel-pro-recipes` â€” file map and recipes (pages, CRUD, forms, API, RBAC, overlays) + commands.

## Hard rules

- **Entry & routes.** [src/main.jsx](mdc:src/main.jsx) mounts `BrowserRouter â†’ AuthProvider â†’ App`. All routes live in [src/App.jsx](mdc:src/App.jsx); protected pages sit under `<RequireAuth><AdminLayout/></RequireAuth>` and are wrapped `guard('<module>:view', <Page/>)`.
- **Folder-per-page.** Each page is `src/pages/<Module>/<Page>/index.jsx` with its subcomponents (`columns.jsx`, `tabs.jsx`) beside it.
- **Reuse, don't hand-roll.** Build lists/forms/overlays from `src/components/crud/*` (`ResourcePage`, `DataTable`, `FormModal`, `FormField`, `FilterBar`, `ConfirmDialog`, `SummaryCard`, `StatusBadge`, `Tabs`, `Dropdown`, `ExportButtons`) and `src/components/*` (`Modal`, `PageHeader`, `Icon`). Toasts via `showToast` from [src/v4/toast.js](mdc:src/v4/toast.js).
- **All backend calls go through the API client.** Import `api` from [src/api/client.js](mdc:src/api/client.js) and put one module per resource in `src/api/`. The base URL lives only in [src/api/config.js](mdc:src/api/config.js) (`VITE_API_BASE_URL`). Never hard-code a backend URL elsewhere. The client auto-attaches the `fp_token` Bearer header and throws on non-2xx / network errors.
- **RBAC everywhere.** Gate routes with `ProtectedRoute perm="<module>:<action>"`, check with `can()` from `useAuth()`, and use `<Can>` for inline UI. The permission matrix is [src/domain/permissions.js](mdc:src/domain/permissions.js).
- **NAV is one constant**: `NAV` in [src/data/nav.js](mdc:src/data/nav.js). Each leaf's `module` matches its route perm. New icons â†’ `Icon` map in [src/components/Icon.jsx](mdc:src/components/Icon.jsx) (inline SVG, `currentColor`).
- **Colors via CSS custom properties** in [src/scss/_tokens.scss](mdc:src/scss/_tokens.scss); never hex literals in components (keeps dark mode working).
- **Subpath-safe URLs.** Use `import.meta.env.BASE_URL` for asset paths; never hard-code a leading `/`.
- **Idempotent, guarded components.** Pages/components must render safely when their data is absent (loading/empty states).
- **No `console.*` in shipped code.**

## Anti-patterns

- Don't add jQuery, Bootstrap, Tailwind, PostCSS, or a state library.
- Don't hand-roll tables, forms, modals, or toasts â€” use the `crud` components.
- Don't `fetch()` a hard-coded backend URL â€” use the `api` client + `src/api/config.js`.
- Don't put a protected page outside `RequireAuth` / `ProtectedRoute`.
- Don't break folder-per-page (no flat `src/pages/Foo.jsx` for new pages).
- Don't use hex colors in components â€” use the `--token` CSS variables.
- Don't edit `dist/`, `node_modules/`, or generated output.
